channel.title: EuroscapePK Webclient (Project Insanity)
channel.description:
*Please do not post any rude comments
[B]Story:[/B] I could never make a webclient (Yes I know "It's soo easy!", but I couldn't do it before. I always had some problem. When I got this one to work, I was excited. So i'll be doing a free webclient service pretty soon, refactored + non refactored.
[B]What it includes:[/B] An open source website of the old RuneScape webclient navbar (Pictures below), open source #474 EuroscapePK made by Affliction.
*I made this because alot of people are using Project Insanity.
[B]Pictures:[/B] [img]http://img535.imageshack.us/img535/2216/loggedin.png[/img] [img]http://img375.imageshack.us/img375/8854/titlec.png[/img]
Downloads: http://uppit.com/xuzaejh2bbdd/Old_Navbar(RS).zip Also, the cache directory default downloads to C:/WINDOWS/.cachePI/, but you can change it. Search "findcachedir()" in signlink.java, "data/" in Class36.java, and "Raw/" in client.java if you're changing the directory, and animation.java.
*Full credits to Affliction. *Credits to me for finding the old shmexy RuneScape nav bar, ;), and for making the webclient. All I did was make a webclient, nothing more.
Oh, and if you need a link to the cache, you can find it here. [url=http://www.mediafire.com/?2yyntnzkkf5]http://www.mediafire.com/?2yyntnzkkf5[/url]
